WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:08.500
<i>♪ La-la-la-la, la-la-la-la ♪</i>

00:08.583 --> 00:09.916
-[grunts]
-Mmm.

00:11.000 --> 00:13.166
[wind swooshing]

00:13.250 --> 00:17.375
[angrily]
Who are you and what do you want?

00:17.458 --> 00:20.666
Great, uh, coldtaurs,

00:20.750 --> 00:24.458
we have traveled for weeks to reach
your cold but beautiful land.

00:24.541 --> 00:28.666
-We have one request for--
-[screeching]

00:28.750 --> 00:30.458
[yelling]

00:30.541 --> 00:33.541
-Horse!
-[yelling]

00:33.625 --> 00:35.375
Help! Help!

00:35.458 --> 00:36.958
I'm being stolen!

00:37.041 --> 00:39.708
The klepto has become the klepted!

00:39.791 --> 00:42.125
-[screeching]
-[grunting]

00:42.208 --> 00:44.375
[intense music playing]

00:44.458 --> 00:45.375
What the…

00:45.458 --> 00:46.875
[music abruptly stops]

00:47.458 --> 00:49.166
We'll be right back. Hang on.

00:50.208 --> 00:52.208
[grunts]

00:55.041 --> 00:58.708
[Wammawink] <i>♪ In Centaurworld</i> ♪

00:58.791 --> 01:01.375
-[neighing]
-[vocalizing]

01:01.458 --> 01:02.625
[squeaks]

01:04.583 --> 01:06.166
[yelling]

01:06.250 --> 01:08.083
-[screeching]
-[groans]

01:08.166 --> 01:10.125
[grunts]

01:10.208 --> 01:12.208
-[snarls]
-[yelling]

01:12.875 --> 01:15.083
[screeching] Thank you.

01:15.166 --> 01:17.000
[grunts]

01:20.250 --> 01:21.875
[whimpers]

01:21.958 --> 01:25.791
[angrily]
Who are you and what do you want?

01:27.458 --> 01:30.916
Ooh! Just kidding.
We know exactly who you are.

01:31.000 --> 01:33.916
Guys, look. Horse is doing the thing!

01:34.000 --> 01:36.166
Did you just say my name?

01:36.250 --> 01:38.166
-[Mouthpiece] Say something.
-No. You talk.

01:38.250 --> 01:41.916
-[Mouthpiece] No. You do it, Old Man.
-Hoo! No, this was your idea, Mouthpiece.

01:42.000 --> 01:43.333
Ugh, fine, okay.

01:43.416 --> 01:46.375
Sorry that was, like, crazy sudden.
We didn't mean to scare you.

01:46.458 --> 01:48.375
We went back and forth on it for a while--

01:48.458 --> 01:49.666
What do you want with us?

01:49.750 --> 01:51.666
Ah! She's just as pushy in real life.

01:51.750 --> 01:53.083
-What the…
-Hey, sorry.

01:53.166 --> 01:56.458
We just had to grab you guys before
you progressed the story any further.

01:56.541 --> 01:59.416
We binge-watched everything
up until "The Rift: Part 2."

01:59.500 --> 02:01.416
"Rift: Part 2"?

02:01.500 --> 02:05.250
It's what we've been calling it. [sighs]
It makes sense if you think about it.

02:05.333 --> 02:09.125
Part 1 was when you got to the Rift.
Part 2 was when you went in.

02:09.208 --> 02:10.625
I'm Hanglydangly.

02:10.708 --> 02:15.208
I run Herd Words, the Message Bird
that's all herd, all the terd.

02:15.291 --> 02:16.916
Where are we exactly?

02:17.000 --> 02:21.833
Um, we're the birdtaurs,
and this is our cloud condo complex.

02:21.916 --> 02:25.208
Wait, so you've been following us
this whole ter… Uh, time?

02:25.291 --> 02:27.375
[yelps, grunts]

02:27.458 --> 02:30.375
Following you? You don't… They don't…

02:30.458 --> 02:31.791
Guys, they don't know.

02:31.875 --> 02:35.375
You don't know that you're
the most watched show in Centaurworld.

02:36.333 --> 02:38.875
I mean, you don't even know how vast

02:38.958 --> 02:41.291
our fan community network
is up here, Horse.

02:41.375 --> 02:44.583
We've got, like, clubs within clubs
just dedicated to you.

02:44.666 --> 02:48.750
We're just like a bunch of newborn baby
birdtaurs hungry to devour your content.

02:48.833 --> 02:51.541
[chuckles]
That's a little weird, but thank you?

02:51.625 --> 02:54.916
<i>♪ We've been watching you</i>
<i>We've been binge-watching you ♪</i>

02:55.000 --> 02:58.291
<i>-♪ We are obsessing every day ♪</i>
-This seems neurotic.

02:58.375 --> 03:01.583
<i>♪ We are fangirling hard</i>
<i>Wrote fiction, made some art ♪</i>

03:01.666 --> 03:03.875
<i>♪ We've shipped you every different way ♪</i>

03:03.958 --> 03:06.250
<i>-♪ But we're platonic ♪</i>
<i>-♪ My name is Mouthpiece</i> <i>♪</i>

03:06.333 --> 03:08.416
<i>♪ But you'd know me by my username ♪</i>

03:08.500 --> 03:11.583
<i>♪ ComfortableDougGuy222</i>
<i>That's when my birthday is ♪</i>

03:11.666 --> 03:14.958
<i>♪ These owl, geese, pheasant</i>
<i>Sparrow, duck and kiwitaurs ♪</i>

03:15.041 --> 03:16.791
<i>♪ Made so much merch outta you ♪</i>

03:16.875 --> 03:18.458
<i>♪ We're in the fandom biz! ♪</i>

03:19.000 --> 03:22.958
<i>♪ So glad Horse made us so sad</i>
<i>That Rider is gone ♪</i>

03:23.041 --> 03:24.291
Where'd that girl go?

03:24.375 --> 03:27.458
<i>♪ What went on inside of the Rift?</i>
<i>Who cares? ♪</i>

03:27.541 --> 03:30.125
<i>-♪ The herd's here for Herd Con! ♪</i>
<i>-♪ What is Herd Con? ♪</i>

03:30.208 --> 03:34.291
<i>♪ We've been binge-watching you</i>
<i>And you're our favorite show that's on ♪</i>

03:34.375 --> 03:37.166
[chuckles]
Well, this is overwhelming, isn't it?

03:37.250 --> 03:41.416
I mean, who knew all this time
that we were celebrities?

03:41.500 --> 03:46.708
Oh, uh, to clarify,
not all of you are celebrities.

03:46.791 --> 03:48.041
What are you saying?

03:48.125 --> 03:51.583
I mean, maybe some of you are,
like, not as popular as others.

03:51.666 --> 03:55.458
Well, I don't understand, Mouthpiece.
You just said we're the most popular--

03:55.541 --> 03:58.666
♪ <i>Well, the Horse Force</i>
<i>Is for the Horse fans, of course ♪</i>

03:58.750 --> 04:01.500
<i>♪ And the Ched Heads</i>
<i>Have the handsomest mugs ♪</i>

04:01.583 --> 04:03.291
<i>-♪ We're Hot Gosslings! ♪</i>
<i>-♪ Team Durp!</i> ♪

04:03.375 --> 04:05.083
<i>♪ Glendale's Pregnancy Hole Children! ♪</i>

04:05.166 --> 04:10.750
<i>♪ And Dougligans are fans</i>
<i>Of the great Comfortable Doug ♪</i>

04:11.500 --> 04:13.500
<i>♪ Comfortable Doug ♪</i>

04:14.125 --> 04:16.125
<i>♪ Comfortable Doug ♪</i>

04:16.208 --> 04:20.041
<i>♪ Comfortable, Comfortable</i>
<i>Comfortable Doug ♪</i>

04:20.125 --> 04:22.166
<i>♪ Comfortable Doug ♪</i>

04:22.250 --> 04:25.375
<i>♪ Comfortable Doug ♪</i>

04:25.458 --> 04:28.333
<i>♪ Comfortable, Comfortable Doug ♪</i>

04:28.416 --> 04:31.041
Okay, okay, okay, okay, I think we get it.
[chuckles]

04:31.125 --> 04:33.875
Ya like Comfortable Doug, Mouthpiece.
[chuckles]

04:33.958 --> 04:36.583
Now, what is
the Wammawink fan club called? Hm?

04:36.666 --> 04:40.166
Who, uh… Whe… Where are
the Wammawink fans, Mouthpiece?

04:40.250 --> 04:43.416
Answer me, Mouthpiece. Mouthpiece!
Why don't you tell me, Mouthpiece?

04:43.500 --> 04:44.625
You're hurting me.

04:44.708 --> 04:47.666
-Oh yeah, she does that sometimes.
-[baby birdtaurs] The hole!

04:47.750 --> 04:51.791
♪ <i>The only thing</i>
<i>Those fan clubs can agree on ♪</i>

04:51.875 --> 04:54.500
<i>♪ Is that Wammawink's ♪</i>

04:55.083 --> 04:59.083
<i>♪ The worst ♪</i>

05:01.958 --> 05:03.458
[inhales, screams]

05:03.541 --> 05:05.583
Horse, this way.
We wanna show you something.

05:06.083 --> 05:10.333
[Mouthpiece] This is our sky door.
From here, we can see all of Centaurworld.

05:10.416 --> 05:13.666
It's how we know all about Rider,
you, Stabby, Gebbrey. [gasping]

05:13.750 --> 05:17.000
Look! The Johnny Teatime's
Be Best Competition is back on!

05:17.916 --> 05:21.000
Ah, guys, check it out.
Comfortable Doug is back.

05:22.750 --> 05:24.125
[dinging]

05:25.416 --> 05:27.583
-Outta the way! [panting]
-[screeches]

05:27.666 --> 05:30.083
[screams] He's so cool!

05:30.166 --> 05:31.916
[panting]

05:32.000 --> 05:34.291
Sure, whatever. Why did you bring us here?

05:34.375 --> 05:36.750
Okay, yeah, yeah, yeah. Stupid Mouthpiece.

05:36.833 --> 05:40.166
So, like I was saying, we didn't get to
see what happened inside the Rift.

05:40.250 --> 05:43.666
Yeah, it was an odd choice to carry out
all of that action off-screen.

05:43.750 --> 05:46.208
Bayden filled us in on the underground
and whale stuff.

05:46.291 --> 05:50.000
But since he saw "The Rift: Part Two"
before we did, he's been real smug.

05:50.083 --> 05:53.625
Yeah, I don't wanna give anything away,
but there's this part where--

05:53.708 --> 05:55.000
Shut up, Bayden.

05:55.083 --> 05:58.208
I don't want your spoilers.
I wanna get it from the horse's mouth.

05:58.291 --> 06:01.250
Wait, you brought us up here
just so I can tell you what happened

06:01.333 --> 06:03.916
-when we were in the Rift?
-Don't you dare tell us!

06:04.000 --> 06:08.083
Sorry, I didn't mean to yell.
I'm just such a fan. Stupid Mouthpiece.

06:08.666 --> 06:14.375
So we thought since you're here,
you could maybe perform what happened.

06:14.458 --> 06:16.375
Now that I'm saying it, it sounds weird.

06:16.458 --> 06:18.708
-I sound stupid, don't I?
-No, dude. Keep going!

06:18.791 --> 06:20.625
Right. Okay. Thanks, Old Man.

06:20.708 --> 06:24.541
We thought you could kind of redo it.
But, like, exactly.

06:24.625 --> 06:27.041
Like, do exactly what happened
inside the Rift.

06:27.125 --> 06:29.333
Sorry, is her name Old Man?

06:29.416 --> 06:30.291
Yes.

06:30.375 --> 06:32.791
And his name is Mouthpiece?

06:32.875 --> 06:34.916
-Yes.
-Okay.

06:35.666 --> 06:37.458
We have to get the <i>flonk</i> out of here.

06:37.541 --> 06:40.916
Normally I'd be with Zulius on this,
but I just had a thought.

06:41.000 --> 06:43.250
They're crazy idiots,
but they picked all of us up

06:43.333 --> 06:45.041
off the ground like we were nothing.

06:45.125 --> 06:47.958
Minotaurs don't fly.
These guys could give us a real advantage.

06:48.041 --> 06:49.000
[panting]

06:49.083 --> 06:53.125
An army in the sky is exactly the kind of
thing Rider is counting on me to deliver.

06:53.708 --> 06:56.666
Look, we need these guys.
Let's just do what they want.

06:56.750 --> 06:59.083
[grunts] Okay. If we're gonna do this,

06:59.166 --> 07:02.625
you must allow me
to stage manage this production.

07:02.708 --> 07:05.166
Stabby's a little young to go onstage.

07:05.250 --> 07:07.916
I'm 43 years old.

07:08.000 --> 07:11.166
And Durpleton 47.

07:11.250 --> 07:12.083
Obvi.

07:12.166 --> 07:14.500
[panting]

07:14.583 --> 07:17.208
-What was I? Ahh!
-[squeaks]

07:17.791 --> 07:20.166
-[squeaks]
-Shouldn't have skipped lung day.

07:20.250 --> 07:22.625
-One and Ched and two and Ched…
-Is that…

07:22.708 --> 07:26.208
-…and three and Ched and four and Ched…
-Is… Is that me?

07:26.291 --> 07:29.666
-Those guys are the Ched Heads.
-Hooray!

07:29.750 --> 07:31.083
Of course they're Ched Heads.

07:31.166 --> 07:34.125
They're birdtaurs. I'm a birdtaur.
They recognize excellence.

07:34.208 --> 07:35.958
-Whatever they want, I'm in.
-We're in.

07:36.041 --> 07:38.416
But you need to do something for us too.

07:38.500 --> 07:39.583
[cheering]

07:39.666 --> 07:42.875
Crandy is gonna flip her feathers!

07:42.958 --> 07:44.333
Uh, who's Crandy?

07:45.250 --> 07:49.166
[gasping]

07:49.250 --> 07:51.333
Then she made
cilantro super popular again.

07:51.416 --> 07:53.541
She's got her own brand
of vegan hair ties.

07:53.625 --> 07:57.333
She runs Herd Con. She went viral, like,
five times for painting her beak.

07:57.416 --> 08:01.250
Oh my goose!
I can't believe you guys are here!

08:01.333 --> 08:03.833
Yep. It's us. Uh, we--

08:03.916 --> 08:07.541
<i>♪ My name is Crandy</i>
<i>And I've got lots of subscribers ♪</i>

08:07.625 --> 08:10.375
<i>♪ They love hearing me say</i>
<i>"Wow! Oh my goose!" ♪</i>

08:10.458 --> 08:13.750
<i>♪ And all my fans react</i>
<i>To all my reenactments ♪</i>

08:13.833 --> 08:16.583
<i>♪ Reenacting my reactions to you ♪</i>

08:16.666 --> 08:18.791
<i>♪ Watching them watching me ♪</i>

08:18.875 --> 08:20.875
<i>♪ Is, like, my favorite thing to do ♪</i>

08:20.958 --> 08:21.791
<i>♪ Yeah! ♪</i>

08:23.541 --> 08:28.625
Okay, well, that was lit, but, uh,
I… I still don't know who you are.

08:28.708 --> 08:30.958
Have you not been paying attention?

08:31.041 --> 08:33.791
Clearly, she's an influencer.

08:33.875 --> 08:35.000
Hold that thought.

08:35.083 --> 08:37.000
Okay, everybody, Crandy-Gram!

08:37.083 --> 08:38.708
-Like!
-Like!

08:38.791 --> 08:41.125
So I just saw the herd
for the first time in person,

08:41.208 --> 08:44.333
and I was like, "Oh my goose."
And then I put my arms out like this,

08:44.416 --> 08:46.791
and then I said,
"I can't believe you guys are here."

08:46.875 --> 08:48.291
And then I sang my Crandy song

08:48.375 --> 08:50.541
and they were all like,
"Your voice is amazing."

08:50.625 --> 08:52.750
-Like!
-Like!

08:52.833 --> 08:53.708
Like!

08:53.791 --> 08:58.208
And don't forget to get your tickets
to Herd Con, like, and subscribe. Bye!

08:58.291 --> 09:00.166
[chuckles] You were saying?

09:01.000 --> 09:03.541
We're down to do this whole
"recap the Rift" situation,

09:03.625 --> 09:06.208
but as you know,
there's a war coming to Centaurworld.

09:06.291 --> 09:07.625
[Horse] The Nowhere King is--

09:07.708 --> 09:11.625
[gasping]

09:11.708 --> 09:13.500
-Gross!
-Aw!

09:13.583 --> 09:14.625
[grunts]

09:14.708 --> 09:18.625
Mouthpiece have message from Crandy.

09:18.708 --> 09:21.375
The herd LOL is here.

09:23.250 --> 09:25.250
[stammering] So, we're building…

09:25.333 --> 09:29.291
We're building an army, and birdtaurs
could be a big asset in the fight.

09:29.375 --> 09:31.166
<i>-Shell-fie!</i>
-[camera shutters]

09:31.708 --> 09:33.208
<i>Shell-fie!</i>

09:33.291 --> 09:35.083
Uh, yeah, sure. Whatever.

09:35.166 --> 09:36.541
Oh. Great!

09:36.625 --> 09:39.541
So you'll join us on the battlefield.
[chuckles]

09:39.625 --> 09:41.250
An army in the skies!

09:41.333 --> 09:44.833
Do you think one minute is enough silence
to honor Waterbaby at her memorial?

09:44.916 --> 09:46.750
[scoffs] Waterbaby's not dead.

09:46.833 --> 09:49.291
[gasping] Oh my goose. Spin-off!

09:49.375 --> 09:51.500
[tense music playing]

09:53.208 --> 09:55.500
[slurping]

10:06.416 --> 10:08.416
[tense music playing]

10:11.166 --> 10:13.041
[squeaks]

10:17.083 --> 10:19.083
[snarls, pops]

10:19.166 --> 10:20.083
[snarls]

10:21.333 --> 10:23.625
-[birds chirping]
-[laughing]

10:24.666 --> 10:27.000
Hey, friends. Look at me!
Look at me! Look at me!

10:27.083 --> 10:29.000
[applauding]

10:31.875 --> 10:33.458
Hey, Crandy, uh,

10:33.541 --> 10:36.916
if we agreed to do the reenactment,
what are we doing this for?

10:37.000 --> 10:40.375
If you want brand loyalty,
you have to give a little fan service.

10:40.458 --> 10:42.333
Oh, who should I make this out to?

10:42.416 --> 10:45.208
Uh, no, those are actually
some catchphrases I had for you.

10:45.291 --> 10:48.458
My favorite is "Oh no, you Durple-didn't."

10:48.541 --> 10:49.666
Oh my.

10:49.750 --> 10:52.833
Look at all these delicious-looking fans.

10:52.916 --> 10:56.458
Hoot! Can you sign my <i>ManSplash</i>?
It's the holiday issue.

10:56.541 --> 11:01.125
[chuckles]
I see you too are a Centaur of taste.

11:01.208 --> 11:03.416
I love to hate-watch you. [chuckles]

11:03.500 --> 11:04.958
-[screaming]
-[evil laughing]

11:05.041 --> 11:06.583
-[rock music playing]
-[gun cocks]

11:11.833 --> 11:13.583
Whoops! Slipped.

11:13.666 --> 11:17.375
Hoo! It's okay. I was getting
your signature ironically anyway.

11:18.000 --> 11:22.416
-Ironically means that--
-I know what ironically means, Glendale!

11:23.208 --> 11:27.458
It means that she did not
actually want your signature.

11:28.083 --> 11:30.375
Sorry, everybody.
That's it for autographs,

11:30.458 --> 11:32.791
but you can catch up with
the herd when they perform

11:32.875 --> 11:37.250
"The Rift: Part 2. The Lost Episode"

11:37.333 --> 11:40.000
in Nest H. [echoing]

11:42.291 --> 11:44.375
This feels really weird. [chuckles]

11:44.458 --> 11:45.875
Because it is weird.

11:45.958 --> 11:49.541
But we need them. And if this is
what it takes, then this is what it takes.

11:49.625 --> 11:52.666
Besides, you make a great Rider.

11:53.166 --> 11:57.666
Oh! It's just a little something
I threw together. It's not much.

11:57.750 --> 12:00.583
Obviously, I could never replace
Rider as your BFF,

12:00.666 --> 12:03.375
-your closest confidant. [chuckles]
-True.

12:04.208 --> 12:05.916
[whimpers]

12:06.000 --> 12:08.291
All right, hi, everybody. Hey!

12:08.375 --> 12:11.375
Listen up. It's 30 seconds to go-time.
Where's the sound guy?

12:11.458 --> 12:13.375
Uh… um…

12:13.458 --> 12:18.208
Th… There's no one else here,
so I guess I am? Big fan, by the way.

12:18.291 --> 12:20.625
[chuckles]
Okay, great. Love the confidence.

12:20.708 --> 12:23.125
Um, we need some music. What do you got?

12:23.208 --> 12:28.125
Um, as far as music goes,
it's pretty limited to this keytar.

12:28.791 --> 12:30.666
All right, out of my way. Let me look.

12:30.750 --> 12:32.708
[electronic sounds]

12:32.791 --> 12:33.625
No.

12:33.708 --> 12:35.666
[electronic sounds]

12:35.750 --> 12:36.708
What? No.

12:36.791 --> 12:39.041
[electronic sounds]

12:39.125 --> 12:40.375
No.

12:40.458 --> 12:43.250
-[electronic sounds]
-Okay, this is all garbage.

12:43.750 --> 12:45.708
I mean, come on. Listen to this crap.

12:45.791 --> 12:47.541
[electronic sounds]

12:47.625 --> 12:50.583
-Do you have anything else?
-Uh, hey, Zulius?

12:50.666 --> 12:52.833
Uh, maybe we don't need it.

12:52.916 --> 12:56.750
Usually we just start singing
and music comes out of nowhere.

12:56.833 --> 13:00.541
Ha! Are you out of your mind?
Look at the size of the crowd out there.

13:00.625 --> 13:04.250
I'm the stage manager.
If this falls apart, it's on me!

13:04.333 --> 13:07.375
♪ <i>The pressure's on</i>
<i>It's opening night ♪</i>

13:07.458 --> 13:10.541
♪ <i>And everything has gotta go just right ♪</i>

13:10.625 --> 13:11.625
Zulius…

13:11.708 --> 13:14.541
♪ <i>I'm the backstage bad boy</i>
<i>You want workin' your show ♪</i>

13:14.625 --> 13:18.333
♪ <i>So get out of my way</i>
<i>And the magic will flow-ow-ow-- ♪</i>

13:18.416 --> 13:20.250
-Zulius. Hey, Zu… Zulius.
-W<i>… </i>What?

13:20.333 --> 13:23.916
Look, let's just keep it simple
and get through this as quickly as we can.

13:24.000 --> 13:28.083
Ugh, fine. I was just trying
to make this <i>flonking</i> awesome,

13:28.166 --> 13:30.375
but, you know, whatever.

13:30.458 --> 13:32.458
"Just get through this
as quickly as we can."

13:32.541 --> 13:33.541
So, sh… Should I--

13:33.625 --> 13:37.166
Okay, look. Just follow
the action onstage. Watch me for changes.

13:37.250 --> 13:39.083
[intense music playing]

13:39.166 --> 13:42.208
[Zulius] Previously on <i>The Herd.</i>

13:42.291 --> 13:46.750
Horse enters the Rift,
where she's reunited with her Rider.

13:46.833 --> 13:49.166
♪ <i>It's you</i>
<i>It's really you ♪</i>

13:49.250 --> 13:51.916
♪ <i>Despite the changes</i>
<i>I would know you anywhere ♪</i>

13:52.000 --> 13:54.583
♪ <i>The voice, the face, the hair</i>
<i>Might all be different ♪</i>

13:54.666 --> 13:55.833
♪ <i>But you're still you ♪</i>

13:55.916 --> 13:59.041
♪ <i>And all I wanna do</i>
<i>Is hold you close again ♪</i>

13:59.125 --> 13:59.958
[murmurs]

14:00.041 --> 14:06.041
<i>♪ I have journeyed from so far</i>
<i>To meet you in the middle ♪</i>

14:06.125 --> 14:07.291
[squeaks]

14:07.375 --> 14:09.375
[crickets chirping]

14:09.916 --> 14:11.291
They embrace,

14:11.375 --> 14:14.375
but their reunion is fleeting,
when suddenly…

14:14.458 --> 14:19.041
<i>♪ I am the Nowhere King ♪</i>

14:19.125 --> 14:22.458
<i>♪ Bum, bum, bum, bum</i>
<i>Bum, bum, bum, bum, bum ♪</i>

14:22.541 --> 14:26.833
<i>♪ And I've come to do jerky things ♪</i>

14:26.916 --> 14:30.166
<i>♪ Bum, bum, bum, bum</i>
<i>Bum, bum, bum, bum, bum ♪</i>

14:30.250 --> 14:33.708
The Nowhere King
nearly devours Horse and Rider.

14:33.791 --> 14:34.875
[evil laughing]

14:34.958 --> 14:37.500
-[Zulius] But alas…
-Eat spear, you terd!

14:37.583 --> 14:40.208
-Ah!
-[Zulius] Rider spears the Nowhere King!

14:40.291 --> 14:42.208
[groans]

14:42.291 --> 14:44.500
Action sound. Action sound with that.

14:45.000 --> 14:46.458
-Please.
-[electronic sounds]

14:46.541 --> 14:48.625
No. No. No. No. Let's just move on.

14:48.708 --> 14:51.791
[Zulius] But the Nowhere King
drifts out of the Rift

14:51.875 --> 14:54.833
-with a creepy, jerk-ish wind.
-[evil laughing]

14:54.916 --> 14:59.916
[Zulius] He drifts all the way,
all the way out of the Rift.

15:00.000 --> 15:00.875
All the way…

15:00.958 --> 15:03.208
-All the way offstage, Durpleton. Thanks.
-Okay.

15:03.291 --> 15:05.250
-[electronic sound]
-[smack]

15:05.333 --> 15:10.416
With the Nowhere King on the loose,
Rider and Horse decide to say farewell.

15:10.500 --> 15:12.458
Rider returning to her world,

15:12.541 --> 15:16.041
and Horse returning to Centaurworld
to help her new friends.

15:16.916 --> 15:22.250
<i>♪ And we'll meet back here eventually ♪</i>

15:22.333 --> 15:23.166
[gruffs]

15:23.250 --> 15:24.958
<i>♪ You've gotta trust me ♪</i>

15:25.041 --> 15:26.416
<i>♪ I do ♪</i>

15:26.500 --> 15:30.041
<i>♪ And what you're saying is true ♪</i>

15:30.125 --> 15:37.125
<i>♪ For you are my closest family ♪</i>

15:38.875 --> 15:40.791
[squeaks]

15:40.875 --> 15:44.833
[soft music playing]

15:48.291 --> 15:51.208
[soft music continues]

15:52.791 --> 15:54.166
[coughing]

15:57.916 --> 15:59.916
[clears throat, gobbles]

16:00.000 --> 16:05.583
Uh, this isn't so much a question
as it is a comment but, uh, like, what?

16:07.000 --> 16:08.583
[whirring]

16:08.666 --> 16:11.125
Okay, great first question.

16:11.208 --> 16:14.333
So the question was, "What?"

16:14.416 --> 16:16.083
What is happening?

16:16.166 --> 16:18.791
There's always a Q and A. Sit down.

16:24.583 --> 16:26.166
Oh, well… [clears throat]

16:26.250 --> 16:28.958
to answer your question, um…

16:29.458 --> 16:30.750
Mhm.

16:30.833 --> 16:32.041
Next question.

16:32.125 --> 16:35.916
Okay, yeah, me. How could you spend all
of that time trying to get to your Rider

16:36.000 --> 16:37.541
and then immediately leave her?

16:37.625 --> 16:39.625
There is a war about to come here,

16:39.708 --> 16:42.250
and the reason we are all doing this
is to ask you all--

16:42.333 --> 16:44.958
Oh, we… Yeah, we know about the war.
But can we go back?

16:45.041 --> 16:47.541
The ending feels retconned.
Anybody else feel that way?

16:47.625 --> 16:49.500
[all chirping]

16:49.583 --> 16:51.125
Yeah, I agree.

16:51.208 --> 16:52.583
Thank you, Durpleton.

16:52.666 --> 16:56.625
Hi, uh, it's me, Mouthpiece, from earlier.
Will there be more Comfortable Doug?

16:56.708 --> 16:58.375
-LOL.
-Great question.

16:58.458 --> 17:01.791
Ugh! Hey, Crandy, are we done here?
We did what we promised.

17:01.875 --> 17:04.583
-[all chattering]
-LOL!

17:06.375 --> 17:08.208
Uh-huh. Yeah, neat. Yeah.

17:09.208 --> 17:12.041
There is a war coming
and we need birdtaurs.

17:12.791 --> 17:14.958
[Horse]
You have wings. You can lift stuff.

17:15.041 --> 17:17.333
If you're willing to fight,
raise your wing.

17:17.416 --> 17:19.750
Put 'em up real high!

17:20.416 --> 17:21.333
Come on!

17:21.416 --> 17:23.583
-[crickets chirping]
-[coughing]

17:23.666 --> 17:28.291
Um, actually, I found Horse deciding
to leave Rider completely unbelievable,

17:28.375 --> 17:31.625
and I have started a petition
to redo the entire ending.

17:31.708 --> 17:35.750
I can't redo it. This is it. It's done.

17:35.833 --> 17:38.333
Okay, raise a wing
if you haven't signed yet.

17:41.125 --> 17:44.541
Cool, cool, cool. Bayden's coming around
with a clipboard to add your names.

17:44.625 --> 17:47.583
-Okay? So…
-Do you think I wanted to leave Rider?

17:47.666 --> 17:49.333
[panting] This is real life.

17:49.416 --> 17:51.666
This was the hardest thing
I've ever had to do

17:51.750 --> 17:54.375
and you're all,
"Why didn't you just do the opposite?"

17:54.458 --> 17:57.125
Hold up. So you are gonna redo the finale?

17:57.208 --> 18:00.083
That wasn't the finale! Ugh!

18:00.166 --> 18:01.458
No more questions.

18:02.250 --> 18:04.958
[soft music begins]

18:05.458 --> 18:10.875
[angry squawking]

18:13.166 --> 18:16.166
Where are you going?
They haven't agreed to join us.

18:16.250 --> 18:19.750
And they aren't going to.
I wanted this to work more than anyone.

18:19.833 --> 18:22.791
[sighs] So much for having
an advantage against the minotaurs.

18:24.875 --> 18:25.916
Okay.

18:26.666 --> 18:28.166
Thank you, everyone.

18:35.541 --> 18:37.750
[Zulius] Horse was right.

18:39.708 --> 18:43.791
We can't change what has already happened.

18:43.875 --> 18:46.750
But you'll never believe
what happens next.

18:46.833 --> 18:48.833
-Like!
-Like!

18:48.916 --> 18:50.458
That wasn't the finale.

18:50.541 --> 18:57.000
"The Rift: Part 2" was really part one
of "The Rise of the Birdtaurs,"

18:57.083 --> 19:00.375
against… Go get your costumes on.
Go! Go! Go! Go!

19:01.125 --> 19:03.000
The Nowhere King!

19:03.083 --> 19:03.916
[squeaks]

19:04.833 --> 19:06.125
[gasping] Told you.

19:06.208 --> 19:10.416
Their gift of flight and bird's-eye sight…

19:10.500 --> 19:15.125
'Twas birds of the wing
that defeated the Nowhere King!

19:15.208 --> 19:18.166
[laughing]

19:20.250 --> 19:22.291
-[shrieks]
-What is he doing?

19:26.041 --> 19:27.750
[explosions]

19:27.833 --> 19:29.083
[screams]

19:29.166 --> 19:32.625
[slow-motion grunts]

19:32.708 --> 19:34.041
[screams, grunts]

19:34.958 --> 19:36.125
[Zulius] But alas,

19:36.208 --> 19:42.125
the Nowhere King was mighty,
but the birdtaurs were so fighty,

19:42.208 --> 19:43.791
they won!

19:43.875 --> 19:45.250
So…

19:45.333 --> 19:46.750
-At least…
-[clucks]

19:46.833 --> 19:49.083
that's how it could end.

19:49.166 --> 19:53.500
You signed this petition
to change the show,

19:53.583 --> 19:58.750
but who wants instead to be <i>in</i> the show?

19:58.833 --> 20:01.333
Come on. Raise those wings.
Let me see 'em.

20:01.416 --> 20:07.458
-Will Horse and Rider be back together?
-Yes, if you come and fight with us.

20:07.541 --> 20:10.041
And you know who else
is gonna be there, Mouthpiece?

20:10.125 --> 20:13.500
Comfortable… Comfortable…
Comfortable Doug's gonna be there.

20:13.583 --> 20:16.208
[gasping] Whoa!

20:16.291 --> 20:17.916
[panting]

20:18.000 --> 20:19.958
Is Wammawink gonna be there?

20:20.041 --> 20:21.291
-Yes.
-Ugh!

20:21.375 --> 20:22.916
-[chattering]
-She's the worst!

20:23.000 --> 20:25.708
But… But… But
she becomes a very minor character.

20:25.791 --> 20:26.916
-[birdtaurs] Like!
-What?

20:27.000 --> 20:29.458
We're so close here.
Just shut up and let me work!

20:30.500 --> 20:33.041
You all have your opinions
for how this should end.

20:33.125 --> 20:37.916
Why not be there for the grand finale
and help us make this story right?

20:39.291 --> 20:41.500
Looks like we're goin' to war!

20:41.583 --> 20:44.958
-[cheering]
-War!

20:45.041 --> 20:46.250
You're welcome.

20:46.333 --> 20:48.166
[cheering]

20:48.250 --> 20:51.833
[screaming]

20:51.916 --> 20:54.458
Hey, I'm one of them too! [grunts]

20:55.541 --> 20:57.541
[squawking]

20:58.958 --> 21:01.791
You guys think I made
the right decision leaving Rider, right?

21:01.875 --> 21:03.916
Oh no, you Durple-didn't!

21:04.000 --> 21:04.916
Durpleton!

21:05.000 --> 21:07.416
These catchphrases are really good.

21:07.500 --> 21:11.250
Of course you made the right decision.
Centaurworld needs you.

21:11.333 --> 21:14.458
[sighs] Does it though?
Zulius did all the work back there.

21:14.541 --> 21:16.166
Thank you, I know.

21:16.250 --> 21:18.666
Horse, you're still the main character.

21:18.750 --> 21:21.083
And I am also a main character!

21:21.166 --> 21:23.375
[screaming]

21:25.875 --> 21:29.708
[panting]

21:36.500 --> 21:37.333
[squeaks]

21:38.333 --> 21:41.416
-[panting, grunts]
-[squeaks]

21:45.708 --> 21:47.375
[low groans]

21:47.458 --> 21:49.208
[electric crackling]

21:52.583 --> 21:54.125
[chitters]

21:56.458 --> 22:00.000
[squeaking]

22:00.875 --> 22:01.708
[whirring]

22:07.416 --> 22:10.208
[electric crackling intensifies]

22:10.291 --> 22:11.708
[whirring]

22:11.791 --> 22:16.250
-[chitters]
-[squeaking]

22:21.166 --> 22:23.916
[sploshing]

22:25.666 --> 22:27.666
[grunts]

22:29.916 --> 22:31.291
[roaring]

22:32.875 --> 22:34.208
[chicken clucking]

22:34.291 --> 22:37.166
-[pigs oinking]
-[growls]

22:37.791 --> 22:39.458
[snarls]

22:41.958 --> 22:43.833
-[low growls]
-[murmurs]

22:43.916 --> 22:45.291
[grunts]

22:47.000 --> 22:49.125
[closing theme music playing]
